WEBVTT

00:01.501 --> 00:03.269
The Pigs: Intruders, Sir!!

00:03.269 --> 00:04.337
The Raccoons!!

00:04.337 --> 00:05.605
Man the defenses!

00:08.842 --> 00:10.477
Alligators!

00:11.511 --> 00:13.013
We've got
to get in there.

00:13.013 --> 00:16.583
But only I, Cyril Sneer,
can get you out!

00:16.583 --> 00:19.519
My fingers are slipping!

00:20.186 --> 00:20.653
or: This is the Evergreen

00:20.653 --> 00:20.787
or: This is the
Evergreen Forest.

00:23.456 --> 00:26.259
Quiet, peaceful, serene.

00:27.861 --> 00:30.263
That is, until
Bert Raccoon wakes up.

00:30.263 --> 00:32.098
Bert Raccoon: Yahoooo!

00:33.867 --> 00:35.635
Yeeeehaaaa!

00:36.236 --> 00:37.470
Yikes!

00:38.071 --> 00:39.372
Yaaaah...

00:41.941 --> 00:43.476
Yeaaaah!

00:43.476 --> 00:46.579
Luckily, he has some
good friends to help him out.

00:53.887 --> 00:56.356
Life would be simple
in the forest except for...

00:57.991 --> 00:59.426
Cyril Sneer!

01:02.862 --> 01:05.031
And his life would be simple
except for...

01:06.032 --> 01:07.333
the Raccoons!!

01:07.333 --> 01:10.303
♪ (show theme music) ♪

01:22.415 --> 01:24.617
Night is coming
to the Evergreen Forest.

01:25.518 --> 01:28.221
The sun sinks slowly
behind the hills.

01:28.221 --> 01:30.256
The birds settle in their nests.

01:31.424 --> 01:32.559
All is peaceful...

01:33.059 --> 01:36.729
Except for the whirring
of the huge machines

01:36.729 --> 01:38.731
in Cyril Sneer's mansion.

01:40.567 --> 01:44.204
This computer
is 6th generation, Ralph.

01:44.204 --> 01:46.172
Sixth generation?

01:46.172 --> 01:48.007
Yeah,
sometimes I think

01:48.007 --> 01:49.742
that it's smarter than Pop.

01:49.742 --> 01:52.512
Yeah, but what
does your Pop think?

01:53.580 --> 01:55.415
(off screen) Pigs!!
The Pigs: Yes, Sir!

01:55.915 --> 01:57.684
(gasps) Pop!

01:57.684 --> 01:59.953
Do you think, he heard us?

02:00.420 --> 02:02.422
If he finds us in here,

02:02.422 --> 02:05.558
I'll be polishing his
armored cars for a month.

02:08.428 --> 02:09.896
Is everything secure?

02:09.896 --> 02:12.632
The Pig: How could an intruder
possibly break through

02:12.632 --> 02:14.834
your security system, Sir?

02:14.834 --> 02:17.370
The double-encoded computer.

02:18.471 --> 02:21.541
The Pig 2: The triple
titanium steel vault!

02:21.541 --> 02:23.309
The Pig 3: And the alligators!

02:23.309 --> 02:25.044
(whispers) Alligators?!

02:25.845 --> 02:28.915
It's absolutely foolproof!

02:28.915 --> 02:32.118
And any intruder will
be grade-A mincemeat

02:32.118 --> 02:34.187
ala Cyril Sneer.

02:36.289 --> 02:39.893
Cyril/The Pigs:

02:39.893 --> 02:41.761
♪ (gentle music) ♪

02:41.761 --> 02:43.363
In the heart of the
Evergreen Forest,

02:43.363 --> 02:46.332
that same night,
Schaeffer, Broo and Sophia

02:46.332 --> 02:48.168
were gathered with
Melissa and Bert

02:48.168 --> 02:50.837
in the Raccoon-dominium
to share a meal.

02:52.839 --> 02:55.842
How much longer are we
gonna wait for Cedric and Ralph?

02:55.842 --> 02:59.012
My stomach's starting
to snarl at me.

03:00.613 --> 03:02.348
I don't understand it.

03:02.348 --> 03:05.118
Cedric knows, we're
having peanut butters stew.

03:05.118 --> 03:08.555
It's not like
either of them to be this late.

03:08.555 --> 03:10.356
Maybe we
should go look for them?

03:10.356 --> 03:11.357
Woof!
Ugh!

03:11.357 --> 03:13.293
On an empty stomach?!

03:13.293 --> 03:14.494
Bert!!

03:14.494 --> 03:16.629
Ah, good idea, good idea!

03:17.931 --> 03:20.333
Yeah, I'll bring
the emergency supplies.

03:23.303 --> 03:26.339
Ah, (chuckles) my stomach and I

03:26.339 --> 03:29.175
are ready for anything now.

03:29.175 --> 03:31.744
♪ (suspenseful music) ♪

03:36.449 --> 03:37.784
The Pig: Oink!!!

03:39.419 --> 03:41.721
Polarizer
perfectly punctual.

03:44.824 --> 03:45.892
Oiiiink!

03:45.892 --> 03:48.161
Trap door tripper timely!

03:48.161 --> 03:49.629
Open the vault!

03:49.629 --> 03:51.831
The Pigs: But Sir!
Move it!

03:51.831 --> 03:54.634
Release time-lock
retro boosters!

03:54.634 --> 03:57.036
Boost forward stabilizers.

03:57.036 --> 03:58.338
On the double!

03:58.338 --> 04:00.173
The Pigs: Yes, Sir!

04:19.092 --> 04:22.328
The Pig: Oh, a
dazzling sight Sir.

04:22.328 --> 04:25.365
It always takes
my breath away, Sir.

04:25.365 --> 04:26.432
Can the gab!

04:27.533 --> 04:29.235
I can't hear my alligators.

04:30.036 --> 04:32.572
Where is the sound
of tails swishing,

04:32.572 --> 04:34.907
jaws snapping, teeth grinding?

04:34.907 --> 04:37.277
I ordered alligators
in that pit!

04:37.277 --> 04:38.578
Where are they?

04:38.578 --> 04:41.047
The Pig: I-I can explain, Sir.

04:43.716 --> 04:45.885
They're not
doing me any good in there.

04:45.885 --> 04:48.388
Get them down there
where they belong.

04:48.388 --> 04:49.389
The Pig: Oink!

04:50.556 --> 04:53.192
The Pigs: Yes, Sir.
Right away, Sir.

04:56.396 --> 04:58.831
Oh, no!
Not the vault.

04:58.831 --> 05:00.099
Why not?

05:02.268 --> 05:04.904
The Pigs:
Intruders, Sir! Intruders!

05:04.904 --> 05:06.272
Run!!

05:25.124 --> 05:29.429
Aha! My security
system is working perfectly.

05:32.298 --> 05:33.633
Man the defenses!

05:38.004 --> 05:39.172
Seal them up!

05:39.172 --> 05:40.973
The Pigs: Yes, Sir, yes Sir!

05:42.241 --> 05:45.611
The Pig 1: Setting time lock!
The Pig 2: Setting time lock.

05:45.611 --> 05:47.447
Function five...

05:47.447 --> 05:51.651
The Pigs:
...four, three, two one!

05:52.819 --> 05:54.487
Uh, hi, Pop!

05:54.487 --> 05:55.855
Cedric!!

05:56.622 --> 05:57.657
Bye, Pop!

05:59.759 --> 06:02.628
Cedric!...My boy!

06:02.628 --> 06:05.331
The Pig 1: The intruders
are trapped, Sir.

06:05.331 --> 06:08.468
The Pig 2: And we've got
the time lock set!

06:08.468 --> 06:11.337
For next Groundhog Day.

06:11.938 --> 06:13.106
Intruder?!

06:13.106 --> 06:15.708
That's no intruder, ham head.

06:15.708 --> 06:17.477
That's my son!

06:17.477 --> 06:20.179
The Pig 3: We were only
following orders, Sir.

06:20.179 --> 06:22.648
The Pig 1: Yes Sir,
your order, Sir.

06:24.217 --> 06:27.353
You know, you'd look good
with an apple in your mouth.

06:27.353 --> 06:29.956
That's my son you've
trapped in there.

06:29.956 --> 06:32.024
The one I built my empire for.

06:32.024 --> 06:34.193
The heir to that very vault!

06:34.994 --> 06:36.863
My Cedric!

06:36.863 --> 06:37.997
The Pig 3: But, Sir...

06:38.498 --> 06:40.400
Get an
apple for his mouth!

06:40.400 --> 06:42.835
The Pig 1: Macintosh
or Delicious, Sir?

06:42.835 --> 06:46.305
Or Spy? Rome, Granny Smith?

06:48.207 --> 06:50.376
There doesn't
seem to be anyone home.

06:50.376 --> 06:51.811
Keep trying, Bert.

06:55.014 --> 06:58.351
The Pig 1: The Raccoons!
It's all your fault!

06:58.351 --> 07:01.053
Who's there?
What do you want?

07:01.053 --> 07:05.057
Excuse me, Mr Sneer,
but is Cedric at home?

07:05.057 --> 07:07.326
No!!
Cedric has gone away.

07:08.327 --> 07:09.195
...to school!

07:09.195 --> 07:10.663
Without
saying goodbye?!

07:10.663 --> 07:11.998
Uh...

07:11.998 --> 07:15.268
He's enrolled in a
night course in uh...

07:15.268 --> 07:16.502
...cost accounting.

07:16.502 --> 07:18.438
Cedric loves cost accounting.

07:20.773 --> 07:22.275
I don't believe him.

07:22.275 --> 07:23.543
Yeah...

07:23.543 --> 07:26.446
Cedric, took
cost accounting last year.

07:26.446 --> 07:29.148
I think Cedric's
inside that house

07:29.148 --> 07:31.050
and I think he's in trouble.

07:31.050 --> 07:33.553
Which means
Ralph's in trouble too.

07:33.553 --> 07:35.788
We've got to get in there.

07:35.788 --> 07:38.524
Yeah! Yeah, but how?

07:38.524 --> 07:40.526
Woof-woof!

07:40.526 --> 07:43.729
Hey, I think
Broo's on to something.

07:47.133 --> 07:50.937
You mean we're locked in
here for the next six months?

07:50.937 --> 07:54.640
No, just 'til
Groundhog Day, right Pop?

07:54.640 --> 07:57.276
Well.. um...
Pipe down!

07:57.276 --> 07:59.245
Can't you see,
I'm trying to think?

08:00.480 --> 08:03.483
Groundhog Day is
a long ways away, Cedric.

08:03.483 --> 08:06.052
Gee, it is, isn't it?

08:06.052 --> 08:08.254
What will we do for food?

08:08.254 --> 08:09.622
Pop?!

08:09.622 --> 08:13.259
Well..I..um..I..ehm...

08:14.760 --> 08:16.562
Pop?

08:23.302 --> 08:25.171
Wait! Hold everything!

08:26.506 --> 08:28.241
This security system
has a built-in

08:28.241 --> 08:30.076
emergency backup device.

08:30.076 --> 08:33.679
The Pigs: (laughs) Good, Sir!
Good thinking, Sir.

08:34.180 --> 08:35.181
Cedric?

08:36.449 --> 08:37.683
Pick up the phone!!

08:37.683 --> 08:39.819
This is highly confidential,

08:39.819 --> 08:41.354
top secret information.

08:42.822 --> 08:46.325
Cedric,
there's a master security key

08:46.325 --> 08:48.160
in that safe behind you.

08:48.728 --> 08:52.298
Now listen very carefully
to the combination.

08:55.868 --> 08:57.403
Speak up, Pop!

08:57.937 --> 09:00.373
I said 22 to the left.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.707
and two to the right.

09:01.707 --> 09:02.708
Right, Pop!

09:02.708 --> 09:04.310
Uhm!

09:05.144 --> 09:06.178
Okay.

09:06.178 --> 09:07.713
♪ (drum roll) ♪

09:08.814 --> 09:11.717
♪ (drum roll) ♪

09:11.717 --> 09:13.452
There's
nothing in there.

09:14.220 --> 09:16.489
Um... it's empty, Pop.

09:19.926 --> 09:22.094
Empty?! Empty?!?

09:22.094 --> 09:24.530
Where's that master key?!

09:24.530 --> 09:26.599
The Pig 3:
Master key?!

09:26.599 --> 09:29.201
Master key? Ohh, that key!

09:29.201 --> 09:32.838
That's no problem Sir,
here's the key!

09:32.838 --> 09:37.176
you said keep it
in a safe place.

09:37.176 --> 09:40.046
Safe, you bacon brain,

09:40.046 --> 09:41.948
I meant in the safe!

09:41.948 --> 09:44.016
That keys up here,

09:44.016 --> 09:47.086
and my son and the safe
are down there!

09:47.086 --> 09:49.589
Pop, Pop,
we just found a lunch

09:49.589 --> 09:52.058
someone left down here! See?

09:52.058 --> 09:54.260
The Pig: Hey, that's my lunch!

09:54.260 --> 09:55.728
So?!

09:55.728 --> 09:57.730
The Pig: So... hi-hi...

09:57.730 --> 09:59.231
I hope he likes it.

09:59.231 --> 10:03.336
Hey, there's a peanut
butter cookie in here too.

10:04.370 --> 10:07.907
Hey! Did I hear someone
mention peanut butter?!

10:07.907 --> 10:10.009
That was Cedric?

10:10.009 --> 10:12.078
Come on, let's go.

10:14.213 --> 10:16.115
It's no use Cedric.

10:16.115 --> 10:18.618
I'm afraid you're trapped.

10:18.618 --> 10:21.687
But Pop, I know
you'll think of something.

10:21.687 --> 10:23.322
I'll stand guard.

10:23.322 --> 10:26.959
The Pig: No one can outsmart
the security system, Sir.

10:26.959 --> 10:31.430
I can! I can outsmart
anything, including myself.

10:31.430 --> 10:33.933
That's my son trapped in there!

10:33.933 --> 10:36.102
We're going to break
into the vault!

10:36.102 --> 10:38.104
The Pig: But that's
impossible, Sir!

10:38.104 --> 10:40.339
(gasps) Cedric.

10:40.339 --> 10:41.907
Ah, Ralph!

10:41.907 --> 10:43.943
Cedric, can you hear me

10:43.943 --> 10:47.313
Sophia?
How did you get in here?

10:47.313 --> 10:48.914
Who's he talking to?

10:48.914 --> 10:52.451
Pop's got the master
key, but it's of no use.

10:52.451 --> 10:55.287
We're 200 feet
down in the earth!

10:55.287 --> 10:58.824
Who are you? Where are
you? Show your faces, cowards!

10:58.824 --> 11:00.559
We've to get that key!

11:00.559 --> 11:02.495
But he, he's got it.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.665
That's right.
Come on, let's go.

11:10.403 --> 11:13.406
The Pig: Boss!!!
Sir, intruders!!

11:14.940 --> 11:16.175
More intruders?

11:16.175 --> 11:18.210
What is this, visitors day?

11:19.545 --> 11:23.516
I told you, Cedric's at school,
you fools! Now get out!

11:23.516 --> 11:26.318
We know Ralph and
Cedric are trapped down there

11:26.318 --> 11:28.754
and we want the key!

11:28.754 --> 11:30.956
My master security key?

11:30.956 --> 11:32.458
I'd rather rot!

11:32.458 --> 11:34.860
Well,
whatever it takes.

11:34.860 --> 11:37.063
I'll get these open.

11:37.063 --> 11:38.531
Nothing to it!!

11:38.531 --> 11:40.966
The Pig: Don't you touch
that door! It's off limits!

11:40.966 --> 11:42.435
Whoops!

11:49.208 --> 11:50.543
Sorry, boss!

11:50.543 --> 11:54.680
You blundering idiot!
When I get my hands on youuu...

11:54.680 --> 11:56.382
The Pig: Uaaaaah!

11:56.382 --> 12:00.519
♪ (dramatic music) ♪

12:00.519 --> 12:02.655
Stick with me, guys. Okay?

12:02.655 --> 12:04.657
We don't
have much choice.

12:05.791 --> 12:08.194
Heyy, this slide
is kind of fun!

12:08.194 --> 12:11.030
Tell it to the
alligators at the bottom!

12:11.030 --> 12:13.199
Aaa-lli-ga-tooors!

12:18.437 --> 12:21.907
♪ (suspenseful music) ♪

12:21.907 --> 12:23.342
Yaaaaah..eh?

12:23.342 --> 12:24.977
Uh-eh-oh!

12:24.977 --> 12:27.379
Don't push! Don't push, Broo!

12:27.379 --> 12:29.648
I'm hanging on as it is.

12:29.648 --> 12:30.616
Woof!

12:31.617 --> 12:32.651
Broo!

12:34.520 --> 12:35.521
Woof-woof!

12:35.521 --> 12:38.357
Get that dog
off my alligators!

12:43.229 --> 12:46.732
He made it.
That a boy, Broo!

12:48.634 --> 12:52.404
Come on, if Broo
can do it, we can do it too!

12:52.404 --> 12:56.275
And get scuff marks
on my brand new alligators?!

12:58.110 --> 13:00.312
We have to do
something, Mr. Sneer,

13:00.312 --> 13:02.515
if we're going to save
Cedric and Ralph.

13:04.817 --> 13:06.919
This is the way to the vault.

13:07.920 --> 13:08.921
Isn't it?

13:10.756 --> 13:12.057
Come on, Bert!

13:13.359 --> 13:15.861
I think, that one's
smiling at me.

13:18.430 --> 13:20.299
Come on, you can do it.

13:26.238 --> 13:28.140
Woah! Yeah! Yikes.

13:28.140 --> 13:32.645
Yikes! Woaaaaah!

13:32.645 --> 13:33.746
Woaaaah!

13:33.746 --> 13:36.148
Someone's been feeding
these alligators

13:36.148 --> 13:37.550
behind my back.

13:38.117 --> 13:39.985
Are you
coming, Mr Sneer,

13:39.985 --> 13:42.888
or do we have to leave
you here alone?

13:43.989 --> 13:46.892
Careful, boys,
I pay your wages.

13:48.594 --> 13:50.696
You gators are getting soft.

13:50.696 --> 13:53.666
Remind me to put you
on a stricter diet.

13:55.301 --> 13:57.002
The Pig: I've got them
on the sonar scanner.

13:57.002 --> 13:59.839
They must have
made it past the alligators.

13:59.839 --> 14:02.341
The Pig: The boss
has it well in hand.

14:03.108 --> 14:09.582
♪ (suspenseful music) ♪

14:09.582 --> 14:12.585
I don't like the
look of this, Melissa.

14:14.620 --> 14:16.589
I think it's a trap!

14:16.589 --> 14:19.325
Of course it's
a trap, you idiot!

14:20.693 --> 14:21.927
I designed it!

14:23.329 --> 14:25.531
The minute you hit
the waterfall,

14:25.531 --> 14:26.732
step to the left!

14:28.033 --> 14:29.301
What?!

14:31.203 --> 14:33.639
Are we gonna trust him?

14:33.639 --> 14:35.741
We have no choice!

14:39.278 --> 14:41.347
Hey, wait! Wait for me.

14:42.982 --> 14:44.650
Yeaaaaah!

14:44.650 --> 14:45.784
Beeeert!!

14:45.784 --> 14:48.354
Uaaaah!

14:48.354 --> 14:49.788
Beeeert!!

14:49.788 --> 14:51.023
Finally!

14:51.023 --> 14:53.826
One of my defenses works!

15:03.903 --> 15:06.906
Melissa?...Broo?

15:06.906 --> 15:08.474
Hurry!

15:08.474 --> 15:11.243
My fingers are slipping!

15:11.744 --> 15:15.748
Bert, Bert,
where are you, Bert?

15:18.651 --> 15:20.286
I can't reach you!

15:21.687 --> 15:24.023
I need something longer.

15:24.023 --> 15:25.758
I need that scarf!

15:26.358 --> 15:27.693
Give that back!

15:33.065 --> 15:36.335
Phew! Ohh safe!

15:36.335 --> 15:38.570
Oh Melissa, how can I...

15:38.570 --> 15:41.106
We don't have time
for sentimental slop,

15:41.106 --> 15:44.009
you feeble excuse for a
fur bearing mammal!!

15:50.783 --> 15:54.453
Don't scream, you idiot.
They react to sound.

16:06.065 --> 16:08.200
No, Broo, don't!

16:16.308 --> 16:17.776
That's it, Broo!

16:17.776 --> 16:19.678
(laughs) Go for it, Broo!

16:21.814 --> 16:24.383
♪ (fast dramatic music) ♪

16:34.093 --> 16:35.961
They sold this
garbage to me

16:35.961 --> 16:38.263
as the ultimate
security system?!

16:38.964 --> 16:40.265
Aaaah!

16:40.265 --> 16:42.468
That was
wonderful, Broo.

16:42.468 --> 16:44.803
Woof-woof!

16:44.803 --> 16:46.772
It's lucky
you're not paid for yet.

16:46.772 --> 16:50.142
Oh, ouch,
ouch, ouch!

16:52.311 --> 16:54.747
That's the
last of it, I'm afraid.

16:54.747 --> 16:56.682
Then you
have it, Cedric.

16:56.682 --> 17:00.219
Maybe we should share
it.. in the morning.

17:01.320 --> 17:02.955
Or next week.

17:12.965 --> 17:14.666
Well, we made it.

17:15.367 --> 17:17.603
Now what?
Now, nothing!

17:17.603 --> 17:20.439
I told you there's no way in!

17:22.041 --> 17:23.375
What is it, Broo?

17:25.210 --> 17:27.513
Eh.. it's
just an air vent.

17:27.513 --> 17:28.947
Just an air vent?!

17:28.947 --> 17:32.451
It's a highly sophisticated
ventilation system.

17:32.451 --> 17:34.620
My mortgages were
getting mildewed!

17:34.620 --> 17:36.722
Well,
where does it go?

17:36.722 --> 17:38.924
To the vault, you fool!

17:38.924 --> 17:40.559
Where else would it go?

17:41.193 --> 17:43.729
Broo, do you think,
you could get through there

17:43.729 --> 17:46.231
and take the key to
Ralph and Cedric?

17:48.567 --> 17:51.336
Mr Sneer!
Quick, bring us the key.

17:54.473 --> 17:57.076
Help you to
break into my own vault?!

17:57.076 --> 17:59.244
What do you think I am?
A complete idiot!?

18:07.386 --> 18:09.855
He's our
only hope, Mr Sneer.

18:10.989 --> 18:15.060
If that dog leaves one hair
in my ventilation shaft...

18:15.060 --> 18:17.629
Well, Broo, good luck.

18:18.363 --> 18:20.432
Broo's gonna be
all right!

18:20.432 --> 18:22.334
Aren't you boy?

18:22.334 --> 18:25.170
♪ (upbeat music) ♪

18:35.547 --> 18:43.021
♪ Hey boy, when your heart is
breakin' ♪

18:43.021 --> 18:46.225
♪ Hey boy, when she's
through takin' ♪

